Each pair of trade signals (BUY signal→SELL signal or SELL signal→BUY signal) constitutes a transaction. “Open transaction” is a transaction which only has one signal. The value of the open transaction may fluctuate with the price of the underlying stock. “Closed transaction” is a transaction that has both (open and close) signals and its value does not change because it is complete. All Profits and Losses are calculated for both open and closed transactions.

Longa uses pay-for-performance service model. The service charges are only applied upon profitable transactions. Longa allows signal providers to charge fees (L-Credits) for each 1% of the profit (Profit Charge). Each signal provider can select a different fee model that corresponds to their signal feed quality and expertise. For example: The signal provider selects to charge 1 L-Credit for each 1% profit (Profit Charge). He provides a buy trade signal when the stock is $100 USD and a sell trade signal when the stock is $110. The calculated profit is 10%. Based on the Profit Charge of 1 LC, the service charge will be 10 L-Credits (1 L-Credits = $1 USD) for every subscriber that has subscribed to the signal feed. If there are 100 subscribers subscribed to this signal feed then the Profit Charge will be 1000 LC less the system charges that amount to 40%, so the total will be 600 LC that can be converted to $600 USD. Please, note that signal providers can define higher Profit Charge to increase their income on profitable signal feeds.
